<recipe>
    <name>Prawns With Thai Sweet Basil Leaves (KAENG PHANAENG KUNG)</name>
    <indexCharacter>P</indexCharacter>
    <notes>THE SAUCE FOR THIS DISH SHOULD BE THICK, HOT AND SWEET SO MAKE SURE YOUR WOK IS HOT ENOUGH TO REDUCE THE COCONUT MILK AS IT HITS THE SURFACE.</notes>
    <servings>4</servings>
    <instructions>PEEL and devein the prawns and cut each prawn along the back so it opens like a butterfly (leave each prawn joined along the base and at the tail, leaving the tail attached).
        
HEAT the oil in a saucepan or wok and stirâ€”fry the dry curry paste over a medium heat for 2 minutes or until fragrant.
        
ADD the coconut milk, fish sauce and palm sugar and cook for a few seconds. Add the prawns and cook for a few minutes or until the prawns are cooked through. Taste, then adjust the seasoning if necessary. Spoon into a serving bowl and garnish with basil leaves and chillies.</instructions>
